=title> Re: RE.</span><hr size=1> I notice that PA is doing *more* damage against some mobs but much less against others of the same con since the patch.  Also, on lucky rolls, the Garrotte/Achilles combo does as much damage as Creeping Death and Stunning Stab. That definetly needs to be tuned.<br>
<br>
Squink, it seems to me that Mythic is trying to give the three Rogues some kind of identity through item bonuses. The highest stealth item I have seen in Hibernia is +2 (No reports from Epic zone yet). There are +3 and +4 stealth in Midguard and Albion. I also believe Hibernia has very few to zero +Crit Strike items, while Midgard has loads of them. What does that leave us? Envenom.<br>
<br>
To me it looks like Mythic is trying to make Hibernia the Envenom realm, and you just said you consider Envenom fluff. I completly agree with you. Envenom is a complete joke with the CS style upgrades. I'm not completly knowledgeable about items in the other realms but they are playing right into our "How should I spec" problem. I also think +2 to a spec is measly in the 45+ range considering you can get +2 steath gear our of Muire and Spraggon.<br>
<br>
I might also push for some kind of definet respec plans. Not just for Rogues but for everyone. The spec lines have been changed so much, especially Nurture, that people aren't playing the characters they started out as. <p><table width="600" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
